  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Boil a full kettle</p><p>Add your <strong>waxy potatoes</strong> to a pot of plenty of <strong>boiled water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, cook for 8-10 min or until just tender, then drain, reserving the pot</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1709311416731-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1709311416731-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1709311416731-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1709311416731-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1709311416731-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>cooked potatoes</strong> to one side of a <strong>tin foil</strong>-lined baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>and put the tray[s] in the oven for an initial 5 min</p><p>Meanwhile, wrap your<strong> basa fillet[s]</strong> in your <strong>smoked</strong> <strong>streaky bacon </strong>– this is your <strong>bacon wrapped basa</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1709311426376-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1709311426376-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1709311426376-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1709311426376-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1709311426376-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the potatoes have had an initial 5 min, transfer the <strong>bacon wrapped basa</strong> to the other side of the baking tray[s]</p><p>Return the tray[s] to the oven for 15-20 min further or until the bacon is crispy and the fish is cooked through – this is your <strong>bacon wrapped basa and roasted potatoes</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked when it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1709311431774-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1709311431774-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1709311431774-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1709311431774-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1709311431774-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the basa is cooking, reboil a full kettle</p><p>Peel and finely slice your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>dill & chive mix</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>Dissolve your <strong>chicken stock mix</strong> in 100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[125ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [150ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong></p>",
